# Server Components for Data Retrieval

All data fetching must happen in **server components**. Never fetch data directly inside client components. All database access — both reads and mutations — must go through **helper functions defined in `db/queries/`**, never inline raw Drizzle queries in pages, components, or server actions.

## Rules

- Mark data-fetching components as `async` server components (no `"use client"` directive)
- Pass fetched data down to client components as props
- Use server actions for mutations, not data fetching
- Never call `fetch`, raw database queries, or server actions that return data from a `"use client"` component
- **All DB reads must call a helper function from `db/queries/`** — never write `db.query.*` or `db.select()` inline in a page or server action
- **All DB mutations must call a helper function from `db/queries/`** — never write `db.insert()`, `db.update()`, or `db.delete()` inline in a server action

## File Structure

```
db/
  index.ts          ← Drizzle client instance
  schema.ts         ← table definitions
  queries/
    decks.ts        ← all deck-related reads & writes
    cards.ts        ← all card-related reads & writes
    ...
```

## Examples

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — db/queries/decks.ts
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decks } from "@/db/schema";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";

export async function getDecksByUser(userId: string) {
  return db.query.decks.findMany({ where: eq(decks.userId, userId) });
}

export async function createDeck(userId: string, title: string) {
  return db.insert(decks).values({ userId, title });
}
```

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — server component calls query helper
// app/decks/page.tsx (no "use client")
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { redirect } from "next/navigation";
import { getDecksByUser } from "@/db/queries/decks";
import { DeckList } from "@/components/DeckList";

export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) redirect("/");

  const decks = await getDecksByUser(userId);
  return <DeckList decks={decks} />;
}
```

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — server action calls mutation helper
"use server";
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { createDeck } from "@/db/queries/decks";

export async function createDeckAction(input: { title: string }) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthenticated");
  await createDeck(userId, input.title);
}
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — raw DB query inline in a page
import { db } from "@/db";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";
import { decks } from "@/db/schema";

export default async function DecksPage() {
  const decks = await db.query.decks.findMany(...); // ❌ inline query
}
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — client component fetching data directly
"use client";
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

export function DeckList() {
  const [decks, setDecks] = useState([]);
  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/api/decks").then(...); // ❌ fetch in client
  }, []);
}
```

## Pattern

```
db/queries/*.ts (helper fns) ← called by →
  Page (server, async) → passes data as props → Client Component (display/interactivity)
  Server Action → calls mutation helper → returns result
```
